adze
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Also early occas. ads, also init. cap. [Spec. use of adze.] An adze-like stone tool from an earlier civilisation, such as the pre-European Maori. a. A Maori stone adze or axe.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
